text.paragraph:
There are no human data with dopamine use in pregnant women. There are risks to the mother and fetus from hypotension associated with shock, which can be fatal if left untreated (see 

                              Clinical Considerations
                           ). In animal reproduction studies, adverse developmental outcomes were observed with intravenous dopamine HCl administration in pregnant rats during organogenesis at doses, on a mcg/m2 basis, of one‑third the human starting dose of 2 mcg/kg/minute (90 mcg/m2/minute).
